<br>
Actually there are two things that might be going on:<br>
<br>
1. SoE goofed, saw the mistake and corrected it without saying anything in the vain hopes no one noticed the screwed up in the first place.<br>
<br>
2. SoE didn't code very good.  It is entirely possible that under the right, or wrong, circumstances their water pet code removes the ability to backstab.  I don't know under what circumstances as I luckily had nothing to do with EQ but as a coder I know you get all sorts of weird bugs at times.  <br>
<br>
So both camps can be right.  If Fin and everyone else don't see a problem anymore then it was probably the 1st one above and we're all saved.  If it crops up every once in a while still then we'll have to learn to deal with it since it's likely they won't try to hunt down an intermitant bug like that. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=zacatac>Zacatac</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Sage</span><br>  Posts: 1564<br> <font color=#333333>(12/30/02 6:57:58 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm46.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=136.topic&index=19>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: no.</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://home1.gte.net/res0v9mh/petblade.jpg" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
